KwaZulu Natal police have appealed to members of the public to assist in finding three-year-old Sphesihle Zama Dlamini. Police Spokesperson Thembeka Mbhele said Zama went missing on Sunday while she was attending a church service at Amandawe. “She was playing with other children, however, when her mother looked for her at about 09:00, the little girl was nowhere to be found,” Mbele said. According to Mbele, she was wearing a pink dress with white stripes and white pumps (shoes) when she disappeared. Mbele said Zama was last seen in the vicinity of a tavern in Slangeni Ward in Amandawe. Anyone who can help the police with information regarding Zama’s disappearance call contact Umzinto Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit Detectives on 062 772 8943 / 084 955 5887. Alternatively they can call Crime Stop on 0860010111 or contact their nearest police station. -TNA Reporter